snippet.title: Tennessee Amber Alert EAS #69
snippet.description:
THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE
TENNESSEE BUREAU OF INVESTIGATION.

AN AMBER ALERT HAS BEEN ISSUED ON BEHALF OF MEMPHIS POLICE
DEPARTMENT FOR MARIAH THOMAS, JAMAIYA THOMAS, CHANCE VEASLEY AND 
KEI'MYIA VEASLEY. THE FOUR SIBLINGS WERE LAST SEEN IN MEMPHIS,
TENNESSEE ON OCTOBER 5, 2021. THE FOUR SIBLINGS MAY BE IN THE 
COMPANY OF JAMISHA THOMAS. JAMISHA THOMAS IS WANTED BY THE MEMPHIS
POLICE DEPARTMENT FOR KIDNAPPING AND AGGRAVATED CHILD ABUSE. 
JAMISHA MAY BE TRAVELING IN A 2002 SILVER FORD EXPLORER WITH 
LOUISIANA TAG 1 8 0 7 7 9 2 3. IF YOU HAVE SEEN THESE FOUR 
SIBLINGS OR JAMISHA THOMAS, PLEASE CONTACT MEMPHIS CRIME STOPPERS 
AT 9 0 1 5 2 8 C A S H OR T B I AT 1 8 0 0 T B I F I N D.
